Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on attack detection and mitigation in cyber-physical control systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper studies the performance and resilience of a cyber-physical control system. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses a Markov decision process formulation to design the optimal attack. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper deals with the impact of false positives and mis-detections on the system performance. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve software design and implementation for the cyber-physical control system.
